HEADWORD: Surbed
<hw>Sur*bed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Surbedded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Surbedding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>sur-</ets> +
<ets>bed</ets>.]</ety> <def>To set edgewise, as a stone; that is, to set
it in a position different from that which it had in the
quarry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It . . . has something of a grain parallel with the horizon, and
therefore should not be <qex>surbedded</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gilbert
White.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surbet</ent>⟦br⟧
